<p>the last high point of the road from traffic owing to observation. Unfortunately that does not apply to stretcher bearers so we got under the wire.</p>
<p>On the way back just as we were getting under the wire he started shelling apparently forward of us in salvoes of three.  We kept on &amp; soon, coming over the rise, saw the shells bursting round the cross roads ahead which is known as the most dangerous spot round here.  One of the three shells [indecipherable] just falling</p>
